  - `share_record_to_user` / revoke: `share-record` supports email, grant/revoke, can-edit, can-share, recursive, and expiration (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:73`).
  - `share_folder_to_grantee`: `share-folder` supports user/team/default account via `-e`, plus manage-records/manage-users (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:92`).
  - `share_record_to_shared_folder`: `share-folder` supports record/default-record via `-r`, plus can-edit/can-share (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:98`).
  - `set_shared_folder_default_share`: Commander models default account and default record separately (`.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:310`, `.venv/lib/python3.14/site-packages/keepercommander/commands/register.py:340`).
  - `discover_shared_folder_acl`: current smoke uses `get <sf_uid>` because Commander has no `share-folder --info` (`scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:252`).
- Gate 3 needs a `vaultSharingLifecycle` scenario using the existing smoke rhythm: validate, plan, apply, discover/verify, clean re-plan, destroy, final rediscover (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:327`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:404`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:413`).
- Minimum viable live scenario: create folders, shared folders, direct record shares, shared-folder grantee shares, shared-folder record shares, and default permissions. To truly cover all variants, use five `share_folders`: grantee-user, grantee-team, record, default-grantee, default-record. Four rows can cover the three outer subtypes, but not both default permission shapes (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:83`, `keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:188`).

### 3. Three-Sprint Slicing Recommendation

**Sprint 7h-42: provider parity**

- V7a: finish the missing diff/mock baseline first. Add sibling diff helpers for `shared_folders`, `share_records`, and `share_folders`, then extend mock state so all four blocks can create/update/delete and re-plan clean.
- V7a tests: separate round-trip tests per block, plus mixed-manifest test proving all four blocks survive apply/discover/re-plan.
- V7b: extend `CommanderCliProvider` with explicit sharing methods over `_run_cmd`, not direct DAG writes. Use stubbed `_run_cmd` tests for the exact argv from the Commander parser cited above.
- V7b must also add discovery normalization from `ls -f --format json`, `get <sf_uid>`, and record `get` output; current sandbox already proves those surfaces are used for smoke (`scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:219`, `scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:252`).
- V7c: wire `keeper-vault-sharing.v1` into `load_declarative_manifest`, `PlanLoadBundle`, `_build_plan`, `_make_provider`, and CLI plan/apply. Current dispatch rejects non-PAM/non-vault families (`keeper_sdk/core/manifest.py:131`).

**Sprint 7h-43: smoke scenario design**

- V8a: add `SharingScenarioSpec` or equivalent next to `VaultScenarioSpec` (`scripts/smoke/scenarios.py:335`).
- V8a fixture: roughly 10 folders, 2 shared folders, 3 direct `share_records`, and 5 `share_folders` if the goal is complete subtype proof.
- V8a verifier: assert ACL rows, default permissions, parent folder placement, and no drift rows after rediscovery. Existing vault verifier’s “compute diff again and fail on create/update/conflict” pattern is reusable (`scripts/smoke/scenarios.py:402`).
- V8b: offline tests must validate manifest shape, typed load, expected diff rows, mock apply, and clean re-plan.
- V8c: reuse profile locks. The harness already locks by tenant, profile, admin config, shared-folder title, KSM app, and project name (`scripts/smoke/README.md:174`).

**Sprint 7h-44: live proof + supported bump**

- V9a: run `python3 scripts/smoke/smoke.py --scenario vaultSharingLifecycle --login-helper env` under the granted live harness discipline. Capture sanitized JSON at `docs/live-proof/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.<pin>.sanitized.json`.
- V9b: bump schema status to `supported`, evidence to that artifact, and `since_pin` to the full `.commander-pin` SHA, following the live-proof checklist (`docs/live-proof/README.md:74`).
- V9b meta-test: assert schema annotation status/evidence/since_pin match the committed artifact and full 40-char pin.
- V9c readonly: completion memo for sharing.v1, with anti-patterns for the next family. V2 identifies `keeper-enterprise.v1` as the next family after sharing (`docs/V2_DECISIONS.md:25`).

### 4. Parent-Decide Items

- Discriminator field: keep `kind`. Schema variants each have a `kind` const, and the typed model uses `Field(discriminator="kind")` (`keeper_sdk/core/schemas/keeper-vault-sharing/keeper-vault-sharing.v1.schema.json:161`, `keeper_sdk/core/sharing_models.py:150`).

